review_blob: With a name like Lucifer, i was expecting a hard, alcoholic beer that would knock me to the floor.  but instead a got a sweet, weissbier taste, with a good aftertaste.  golden in color, good head, and very easy to drink.  having another one later =)

Although this beer tastes more like a cider, i give it high ratings!! Golden in color, very light, no head, but wow the taste!! i could not get enough of it..more like an occasion, as the taste i would imagine, get boring after 3 of them.  HIGHLY recommend this beer for after supper.

This is truly a "party beer"  golden in color, good aroma and easy to drink.  If you are looking for a beer that you can drink a lot of and not get tired of the taste, then look no further!!!

rich body, watery at the end.

Stout beer, black in color, good head, VERY good aroma.  Glides down your throat like guinness, but is very differnt taste wise.  Despite all the good things about this beer, i would never buy one again.  Horrible aftertaste, and lingering stench if you get it on your hands.

Very sweet beer, nice to taste, and nice to look at.  Cant have more than one in sitting though.  More like an occasion beer, than a get together beer.  Will definately buy again and enjoy with a cigar sometime.

really did not enjoy this beer, very bland, boring, no taste to speak of. no head, no good aftertaste.
i dont recommend this beer at all.
i enojyed this beer, did not finish it however, got very metallic taste near the end.  Dark in color, a true ale.

golden in color, very easy drinking.  glides down your throat.

i highly recommend this beer on a sunday with a BBQ

Like drinking camel piss, not that i have done that, but i can imagine that it what it would taste like.  Horrible beer, i recommed that you try it, just to appreciate what good beer tastes like.  i reckon this beer was made with water, and chemicals, with some rhino piss added in for body.
Very very nice beer, same taste as the 10, but not as powerfull...strong, dark, no head to speak off...god bless those monks.
Very nice, slow drinking beer. very standard. golden in color, and has a nice hoppy taste.

i love this beer, i prefer to think of it as a shooter before i start my real drinking..and it does smell like old feet!!!!
golden in color, very very smooth and good head.
\m/
Brewed on my homeground, very near to where i live.  Pleasing to drink only when you are at a sporting event, on tap, not out of a can.  Golden and very bloating.
I would only drink this beer, if i could not afford or find guinness.  Yellow in color, not the most pleasing beer out there.  good if you are planning in on getting pissed.
I enjoy this beer on a regular basis, very creamy, aromatic and lusty.  Golden in color, nice head.  If you have not tried it, do so! :)
The Original.  There is nothing that I can say to make you all feel what I feel for this beer.  100% in my book, and will always be!!!!  Bottom Line:  I have a keg at my place :)
i was not really impressed with this beer.  Dark ale looking, very strong..would not buy another one.
I really had a good time with this beer, i took it out, wined and dined it.  Nice and dark, fruity, a bit deep at times.  Bottom line, i would buy it again.
I really enjoyed this beer, very nice on the throat, very smooth, dark in color.  Looks like a cheap beer by the label, ha ha, really enjoyed it.  Bottom line, i would buy a case for home.

Very nice beer, although i must say that if i was going out for a couple of drinks one nite, i would not order this beer.  More of a special occasion kind of beer, the sipping kind.  Strong alcohol taste, not very pleasing on the back of your throat. \m/
